    <h3>The Kalman gain</h3>
    <p>K = P_predicted * H' * (H * P_predicted * H' + R)^(-1). Here P is the error covariance, H is the measurement matrix, and R is the measurement noise covariance. When R is large (noisy sensor), K is small and the filter mostly trusts the model. When P is large (uncertain model), K is large and the filter mostly trusts the measurement. Over time, P shrinks and the estimate converges.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Scalar Kalman filter: estimate a constant from noisy measurements
; True value: 42.0
; Measurement noise variance R = 25.0

(define true-value 42.0)
(define R 25.0)  ; measurement noise variance
(define Q 0.01)  ; process noise variance (small, nearly constant)

(define (kalman x-est P measurement)
  (let* (;; Predict (constant model: x-predicted = x-est)
         (x-pred x-est)
         (P-pred (+ P Q))
         ;; Update
         (K (/ P-pred (+ P-pred R)))
         (innovation (- measurement x-pred))
         (x-new (+ x-pred (* K innovation)))
         (P-new (* (- 1.0 K) P-pred)))
    (list x-new P-new K)))

; Simulate noisy measurements around true value
(define measurements
  (list 47 38 51 35 44 39 48 36 43 41 45 40 42 38 44))

(define (run-filter measurements x-est P step)
  (if (null? measurements)
    (begin (display "Final estimate: ") (display x-est)
           (display " (true: ") (display true-value) (display ")") (newline))
    (let* ((z (car measurements))
           (result (kalman x-est P z))
           (new-x (car result))
           (new-P (car (cdr result)))
           (K (car (cdr (cdr result)))))
      (display "  z=") (display z)
      (display "  est=") (display new-x)
      (display "  K=") (display K) (newline)
      (run-filter (cdr measurements) new-x new-P (+ step 1)))))

(display "Kalman filter (true=42):") (newline)
(run-filter measurements 50.0 100.0 0)
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Scalar Kalman filter
true_value = 42.0
R = 25.0   # measurement noise variance
Q = 0.01   # process noise variance

measurements = [47, 38, 51, 35, 44, 39, 48, 36, 43, 41, 45, 40, 42, 38, 44]

x_est = 50.0  # initial guess
P = 100.0     # initial uncertainty

print("Kalman filter (true=42):")
for i, z in enumerate(measurements):
    # Predict
    P_pred = P + Q
    # Update
    K = P_pred / (P_pred + R)
    x_est = x_est + K * (z - x_est)
    P = (1 - K) * P_pred
    print(f"  step={i:2d}  z={z}  est={x_est:.2f}  K={K:.3f}  P={P:.2f}")

print(f"Final estimate: {x_est:.2f} (true: {true_value})")
`} />
